  "title": "Sales Manager (Tuas, Mechanical/Industrial)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Formulate and roll out commercial plans to expand market presence for mechanical and industrial solutions.</li><li>Guide and support a team of sales personnel to meet organisational goals and revenue expectations.</li><li>Offer technically grounded advice to customers on machinery, engineered components, and system configurations.</li><li>Build new business pipelines while strengthening ties with existing partners and industry contacts.</li><li>Prepare project briefs, cost proposals, and sales materials with accurate technical inputs.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Mechanical Engineering or a relevant engineering discipline.</li><li>At least 5 years of experience in commercial or business development roles within <strong>mechanical/industrial sectors.</strong></li><li>Strong understanding of<strong> mechanical systems, equipment, and engineered products.</strong></li><li>Demonstrated ability to advise clients on technical matters and propose tailored solutions.</li><li>Experience supervising sales teams and achieving commercial targets.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p><p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
